cipation.\n\nIn the window: a stranger who survived. No mask. No polish. Just someone caught between two worlds with nothing but glass between them.\n\nI breathe in through my nose. Hold it. Let it out slow.\n\nThe old reflex kicks in\u2014smooth my sleeves, find the next line, fill the silence with something clean and controlled. My fingers twitch.\n\nI stop halfway. Let my arms hang.\n\nThen the lights cut out.\n\nAll of them. The corridor behind me. The emergency strips along the floor. Even the faint glow from the stairwell where Mara descended.\n\nIn the darkness, something moves in the water outside. Too deliberate to be debris. Too large to be anything I want to see clearly.\n\nThe intercom crackles once. Goes silent.\n\nMy hand finds the wall. Metal cold enough to burn.\n\nSomewhere below, a door slams shut with the kind of finality that locks from the outside.",
